    strong_answer: `"Freshworks has three main products. Freshdesk is their support platform — managing customer tickets across email, chat, and phone. Freshsales is their CRM for sales pipeline and lead management. Freshservice is their ITSM tool — managing IT tickets, incidents, and asset tracking for internal teams. As an SE, I'd focus where the technical integration complexity is highest. Freshservice interests me most because ITSM customers have complex internal workflows — they need to integrate with Active Directory, monitoring tools like PagerDuty, and CMDB systems. That kind of multi-system integration is where an SE adds the most value. Freshdesk is also technically rich with webhook and automation depth. The SE's value at Freshworks is making these integrations seamless across the customer's existing tech stack."`,
